Your solution doesn't work.  It'd be harder to go from a 30-31 on 6d6 than from
a 31-32...

We could use a flat % chance of increasing the ability.  That doesn't allow for
open-ended rolls, but no PC should EVER have skills anywhere NEAR 100 anyway...

For all practical purposes, short of leaving it completely open-ended for
application in a super-heroes game, this works.



